The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 03 January is 152,719 (17,601.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 29 December, there were 11,148 new confirmed cases (1,284.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 22 December, there were 8,614 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 29% (2,534 extra cases).
